  "prompt": "In SimCity BuildIt, how important is it to build the airport?",
  "response": "In SimCity BuildIt, the airport is quite important for several reasons:\n\n1. Population Growth: The airport helps increase your city's population capacity.\n\n2. Specific Achievements: Some city achievements and challenges require having an airport.\n\n3. Tourism: It can help generate additional income through tourism.\n\n4. Trade: The airport provides additional opportunities for trading and obtaining resources.\n\n5. Prestige: It's considered a desirable landmark that can improve your city's overall rating.\n\nWhile not absolutely critical to gameplay, the airport is generally recommended as a beneficial building that can help improve your city's development and performance. Most players find it useful to build an airport once they have the necessary population and resources.",
